# LightS Synthetic Monitoring

LightS Synthetic Monitoring is a web solution for monitoring AWS websites for availability and load performance.

You can deploy LightS Synthetic Monitoring directly from your AWS account using the dedicated wizard.

### 1. Deploy a LightS stack

Click this button to launch the LightS stack in AWS.

[![Launch Lights from AWS](https://dytvr9ot2sszz.cloudfront.net/logz-docs/lights/LightS-button.png)](https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/home?region=us-east-1#/stacks/new?stackName=logzio-sm-light&templateURL=https://sm-template.s3.amazonaws.com/auto-deployment.yaml)

We recommend that you keep the defaults and click **Next** to create the stack and move to the next step. 

![Launch Lights from AWS](https://dytvr9ot2sszz.cloudfront.net/logz-docs/lights/LightS-create-stack.png)

### 2. Configure the stack

Fill in the parameters requested by the form.  

![Launch Lights from AWS](https://dytvr9ot2sszz.cloudfront.net/logz-docs/lights/LightS-stack-details.png)

| Parameter | Description | 
|---|---|
| logzioLogsToken | Token for shipping logs to your Logz.io account. |
| logzioMetricsToken | Token for shipping metrics to your Logz.io account. |
| logzioURL | Logz.io listener URL. [Learn more](https://docs.logz.io/user-guide/accounts/account-region.html#regions-and-urls) | 
| regions | A comma separated list of AWS regions for deployment, (example: us-east-1,ap-south-1) |
| shippingProtocol | Protocol for shipping metrics and logs. 
(Default: https) |
| url | The URL you want to monitor. Example: https://www.logz.io |

### 3. Add tags to your stack (_Optional_)

You can provide tags to help you easily identify your Lambda function. Click **Next** when done.

![Launch Lights from AWS](https://dytvr9ot2sszz.cloudfront.net/logz-docs/lights/LightS-configure-stack.png)

### 4. Confirm IAM Role permissions and create the stack 

AWS will automatically show a notice requesting that you acknowledge that AWS CloudFormation might create IAM resources. 

![AWS IAM Role notice](https://dytvr9ot2sszz.cloudfront.net/logz-docs/lights/LightS-IAM-role-notice.png)

Check the box to acknowledge this option and click **Create stack**.

### 5. Open your Synthetic Monitoring dashboard in Logz.io

Give your metrics some time to get from your system to ours, and then open [Logz.io Metrics](https://app.logz.io/#/dashboard/grafana/).

Your metrics should appear in the preconfigured dashboard in your Metrics account. Use the Synthetic Monitoring Dashboard to monitor your website performance and availability via Logz.io.  
